value: I looked at the starting X and tried to determine if a guaranteed win was possible in 4 more moves. Based on the current status of the game, I felt that that starting position wouldn't guarantee a win because every possible win scenario could easily be blocked by O (diagonally or horizontally).
I used O to block every possible win for X until I came to a sequence that led to O having two blocks and only one move.
placed O to block X until X made 4 in a row
If X played that move then O could block him and still block X on his next move and X would not be able to win yet
I knew O would block the immediate win so I tried different x's from there.
If 'X' played D6 'O' could still block him on his next turn. The quickest way for 'X' to win was playing in the A column to create four in a row.
Since O is forced to answer X from the very beginning, it is very easy to force a win even within 4 turns. The important thing is to keep as many options open as possible.
